==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Samarium
<hw>Sa*ma"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. E.
<ets>samar</ets>skite.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare metallic
element of doubtful identity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Samarium was discovered, by means of spectrum analysis,
in certain minerals (<xex>samarskite</xex>, <xex>cerite</xex>, etc.), in
which it is associated with other elements of the earthy group. It has
been confounded with the doubtful elements <xex>decipium</xex>,
<xex>philippium</xex>, etc., and is possibly a complex mixture of
elements not as yet clearly identified. Symbol Sm. Provisional atomic
weight 150.2.</note> <-- a true element. Symb. Sa or Sm; At. No. 62; At.
wt. 150.43. Valence 2 or 3. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Samaroid</ent>⟦br⟧
